Document: SoftBody3D
Path: godot/classes/class_softbody3d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of the SoftBody3D node, including collision settings, physical characteristics, and simulation parameters.

**collision_layer** (int): The physics layers this SoftBody3D is in. Collision objects can exist in one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_mask. Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans. Default: 1.

**collision_mask** (int): The physics layers this SoftBody3D scans. Collision objects can scan one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_layer. Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans. Default: 1.

**damping_coefficient** (float): The body's damping coefficient. Higher values will slow down the body more noticeably when forces are applied. Default: 0.01.

**disable_mode** (DisableMode): Defines the behavior in physics when Node.process_mode is set to Node.PROCESS_MODE_DISABLED. Default: 0.

**drag_coefficient** (float): The body's drag coefficient. Higher values increase this body's air resistance. Note: This value is currently unused by Godot's default physics implementation. Default: 0.0.

**linear_stiffness** (float): Higher values will result in a stiffer body, while lower values will increase the body's ability to bend. The value can be between 0.0 and 1.0 (inclusive). Default: 0.5.

**parent_collision_ignore** (NodePath): NodePath to a CollisionObject3D this SoftBody3D should avoid clipping. Default: NodePath("").

**pressure_coefficient** (float): The pressure coefficient of this soft body. Simulate pressure build-up from inside this body. Higher values increase the strength of this effect. Default: 0.0.

**ray_pickable** (bool): If true, the SoftBody3D will respond to RayCast3Ds. Default: true.

**shrinking_factor** (float): Scales the rest lengths of SoftBody3D's edge constraints. Positive values shrink the mesh, while negative values expand it. For example, a value of 0.1 shortens the edges of the mesh by 10%, while -0.1 expands the edges by 10%. Note: shrinking_factor is best used on surface meshes with pinned points. Default: 0.0.

**simulation_precision** (int): Increasing this value will improve the resulting simulation, but can affect performance. Use with care. Default: 5.

**total_mass** (float): The SoftBody3D's mass. Default: 1.0.
---CHUNK---
Document: SoftBody3D
Path: godot/classes/class_softbody3d.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing collisions, applying forces and impulses, and manipulating points on a SoftBody3D.

Method: add_collision_exception_with(body: Node) -> void
Adds a body to the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

Method: apply_central_force(force: Vector3) -> void
Distributes and applies a force to all points. A force is time dependent and meant to be applied every physics update.

Method: apply_central_impulse(impulse: Vector3) -> void
Distributes and applies an impulse to all points. An impulse is time-independent! Applying an impulse every frame would result in a framerate-dependent force. For this reason, it should only be used when simulating one-time impacts (use the "_force" functions otherwise).

Method: apply_force(point_index: int, force: Vector3) -> void
Applies a force to a point. A force is time dependent and meant to be applied every physics update.

Method: apply_impulse(point_index: int, impulse: Vector3) -> void
Applies an impulse to a point. An impulse is time-independent! Applying an impulse every frame would result in a framerate-dependent force. For this reason, it should only be used when simulating one-time impacts (use the "_force" functions otherwise).

Method: get_collision_exceptions() -> Array[PhysicsBody3D]
Returns an array of nodes that were added as collision exceptions for this body.

Method: get_collision_layer_value(layer_number: int) -> bool
Returns whether or not the specified layer of the collision_layer is enabled, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: get_collision_mask_value(layer_number: int) -> bool
Returns whether or not the specified layer of the collision_mask is enabled, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: get_physics_rid() -> RID
Returns the internal RID used by the PhysicsServer3D for this body.

Method: get_point_transform(point_index: int) -> Vector3
Returns local translation of a vertex in the surface array.

Method: is_point_pinned(point_index: int) -> bool
Returns true if vertex is set to pinned.

Method: remove_collision_exception_with(body: Node) -> void
Removes a body from the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

Method: set_collision_layer_value(layer_number: int, value: bool) -> void
Based on value, enables or disables the specified layer in the collision_layer, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: set_collision_mask_value(layer_number: int, value: bool) -> void
Based on value, enables or disables the specified layer in the collision_mask, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: set_point_pinned(point_index: int, pinned: bool, attachment_path: NodePath = NodePath(""), insert_at: int = -1) -> void
Sets the pinned state of a surface vertex. When set to true, the optional attachment_path can define a Node3D the pinned vertex will be attached to.